Google App Engine Java Runtime SDK - OAuth Demo

The OAuth demo illustrates how to access user's data through the Google Data
APIs by authorizing with OAuth.

For an introduction to the OAuth protocol, I recommend reading the explanation
from Eran Hammer-Lahav's blog:

http://www.hueniverse.com/hueniverse/2007/10/beginners-gui-1.html

The following sections of the OAuth spec are also helpful in learning about
how OAuth works: 

http://oauth.net/core/1.0/#anchor9
http://oauth.net/core/1.0/#anchor25 

This sample uses the Google Data Java client library which is available here:

http://code.google.com/p/gdata-java-client/

To get all of the dependencies on a Mac OS X, Linux, or other Unix derived
system, you can use the following commands:

wget http://gdata-java-client.googlecode.com/files/gdata-samples.java-1.30.0.java.zip
unzip gdata-samples.java-1.30.0.java.zip
cp gdata/java/lib/gdata-*.jar ./war/WEB-INF/lib/.
wget http://mirrors.ibiblio.org/pub/mirrors/maven2/commons-lang/commons-lang/2.4/commons-lang-2.4.jar
mv commons-lang-2.4.jar ./war/WEB-INF/lib/.
